== Cilantro Yogurt Sauce ==

Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tablespoon} and cilantro. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chickpea Curry ==

In a #large pan{}, combine chickpeas, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, @curry sauce base{5%ounce}, @water{1/4%cup}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then stir in @spinach{5%ounce}. Reduce to a low simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce has thickened and spinach has wilted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> If the spinach doesn't fit all at once, add a handful at a time until it wilts down.

== Rice ==

While curry cooks, massage @microwavable rice{1} in package to break up grains; partially open package. Microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds}.

> Microwave times may vary. Be careful when handling and opening the pouch—steam may release!

== To Serve ==

Divide rice and curry between shallow bowls in separate sections. Top with cilantro yogurt sauce and as many @?sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} as you like. Serve.